Component Architecture

CharacterPicker Component





Sprite Toggle Tabs: Three tabs (8-bit, FF7, FF7 Rebirth) to switch sprite views



Sprite Display: Large centered sprite image that updates based on selected tab



State Management: Uses React useState to track active sprite style



Animations: Fade/scale transitions when switching between sprite styles



Placeholder: Shows placeholder image or message until actual sprites are provided

SkillsCharts Component





Soft Skills Spider Chart: 





7 skills displayed on radar/spider chart



Skills: Communication, Leadership, Problem-Solving, Adaptability, Negotiation, Conflict Resolution, Emotional Intelligence



Scale: 0-100



Hard Skills Bar Chart:





5 skills displayed as horizontal bars



Skills: Planning & Organization, Risk Management, Time Management, Stakeholder Management, Methodologies & Tools



Scale: 0-100



Data Structure: TypeScript interfaces for type safety



Placeholder Data: Initial values set to 0 or placeholder numbers until real data provided

Layout





Side-by-Side Layout: 





Left side: Character picker (40-50% width)



Right side: Skills charts (50-60% width)



Responsive: Stacks vertically on mobile



Dark Theme: FF7-inspired dark color palette (dark blues, greens, mako-like colors)



Animations: Page load animations, chart reveal animations

Data Structure

interface SoftSkill {
  name: string;
  value: number; // 0-100
}

interface HardSkill {
  name: string;
  value: number; // 0-100
}

interface SkillsData {
  softSkills: SoftSkill[];
  hardSkills: HardSkill[];
}

Implementation Details

Styling Approach





Dark theme with FF7 color palette



RPG-style UI elements (borders, fonts)



Smooth transitions and hover effects



Responsive design for mobile/tablet/desktop

Animation Strategy





Character sprite: Fade/scale transition on tab change



Charts: Staggered reveal animation on page load



Bars: Animate from 0 to target value



Spider chart: Draw animation on mount

Image Handling





Placeholder structure ready for sprite images



Support for different image formats (PNG, WebP)



Optimized loading with lazy loading if needed

Development Phases





Project Setup: Initialize React + TypeScript + Vite project with dependencies



Layout & Styling: Create dark theme, side-by-side layout, responsive design



Character Picker: Implement tab interface and sprite switching with animations



Skills Charts: Build spider chart and bar chart components with Recharts



Integration: Connect components, add animations, polish UI



Placeholder Data: Set up data structure for easy skill value updates later

Dependencies





react, react-dom



typescript



vite



@vitejs/plugin-react



recharts



framer-motion



react-icons (optional, for UI elements)

Notes





Sprite images will be added later - placeholder structure prepared



Skill values will be provided later - data structure ready for easy updates



All components will be fully typed with TypeScript



Code will be modular and maintainable for future enhancements

